HEADWORD: Ring winding
<hw>Ring winding</hw>. <fld>(Elec.)</fld> <def>Armature winding in which
the wire is wound round the outer and inner surfaces alternately of an
annular or cylindrical core.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

